88
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:28,800
'My grandson is a real man now.'

89
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:41,400
Grandma.

90
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,360
Let's go.

91
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,640
I'll take you home.

92
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:12,920
Go home.

93
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,880
Go home.

94
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,800
Really.

95
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,520
Can't we talk about something happy when we're out together?

96
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:44,000
The road is still so long.

97
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,730
Even breaking up isn't as devastating as your story.

98
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:49,680
Yaoyao.

99
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,880
Hurry up and wipe your tears.

100
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:53,280
Who knows what else he's going to say later.

101
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:09,120
This is the Tan Kah Kee Memorial Museum.

102
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,960
Dressing like this,

103
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:15,290
