104
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,760
Let's go.

105
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:21,520
What 'play' did you just say?

106
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:22,400
Cosplay.

107
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,400
Cos what?

108
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,600
Cosplay.

109
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,320
This way, please, you three.

110
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,160
Hi.

111
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,039
This way.

112
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,320
And this is

113
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,720
the famous patriotic overseas Chinese leader,

114
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,120
Mr. Tan Kah Kee.

115
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,760
Mr. Tan Kah Kee.

116
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:55,880
He didn't just found and donate to schools,

117
00:08:56,400 --> 00:09:00,600
he called on all of us Nanyang overseas Chinese to unite,

118
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,280
donate money and materials,

119
00:09:03,280 --> 00:09:05,280
and raise funds to save the country.

120
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:07,000
He called on us

121
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:11,530
to return to our country to transport supplies and support the war of resistance.

122
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,760
He made us firmly believe that

123
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,560
as long as we persist,

124
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:17,420
victory will eventually be ours.

125
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,720
This way, please, you three.

126
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:32,000
Look here, everyone.

127
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:34,560
These are some photos of the overseas Chinese mechanics

128
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:37,220
after they returned to their country back then.

129
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,560
Old antique.

130
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,060
So this medal is what you've been protecting all along.

131
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,200
This,

132
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:04,080
this is my faith.

133
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,320
It turns out

134
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,920
firm faith can make a person so strong.

135
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:17,720
These,

136
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,440
these are my comrades-in-arms.

137
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,320
These are my brothers.

138
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,520
Azu, save me.

139
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,800
On October 29, 2022,

140
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:41,080
